nib.text:
Eight people were displaced in a Lyndale apartment fire early Saturday morning, firefighters say. 

At 5:18 a.m., firefighters responded to a report of a fire in an apartment building near South Pleasant Avenue and West 31st Street. 

Upon arrival, they observed flames on a balcony of a third-floor apartment. 

Firefighters evacuated the building and began working to extinguish the blaze. 

By 5:35 a.m., the bulk of the fire had been extinguished and firefighters began to ventilate smoke from apartments and search for any additional signs of fire or any remaining occupants.

In an update, Minneapolis Fire officials said the apartment that contained most of the fire was uninhabitable. 

Two adults and six children were displaced as a result of the blaze and have requested Red Cross assistance. 

No injuries were reported and the cause of the fire is under investigation.

-MbODjXn7055xZx5GQeH.text: According to police reports, units in the area are engaged in the pursuit of a stolen blue Toyota Camry which is said to be headed westbound on University Avenue East.

-MbODpa-JhfO2sYRgtoQ.text: The address reported for this incident has changed to Marion St & University Ave W.

-MbOLsyNuLb1XDwothhj.text: The address reported for this incident has changed to Kent St & Lafond Ave.

-MbOLtJ0JO3W_TDWNw94.text: According to reports from police units, the pursuit of the stolen vehicle ended with the stolen vehicle crashing in the vicinity, and up to four teenage suspects were apprehended after a short foot chase that ensued thereafter.

-MbOLyBJWQexm-33Q64p.text: EMS was also requested to the scene for two of the suspects who are said to have sustained minor injuries as a result of the collision.
